When I write code, it&#x27;s code. I don&#x27;t read it like a human readable text. Because of that, I don&#x27;t really care what it reads when I try to read it as a human readable text.<p>For example I don&#x27;t even think about what it would mean in English if I write<p><pre><code>     while(true){ i++; if(i>100) break; }
</code></pre>
I&#x27;m curious if native English speakers look at code as real English text sometimes? It should be funny, because when I translate my code to my native language(word-by-word) it&#x27;s just meaningless and funny.
